00040 #ifndef __PTLRPC_GSS_GSS_ERR_H_
00041 #define __PTLRPC_GSS_GSS_ERR_H_
00042 
00043 typedef unsigned int OM_uint32;
00044 
00045 /*
00046  * Flag bits for context-level services.
00047  */
00048 #define GSS_C_DELEG_FLAG        (1)
00049 #define GSS_C_MUTUAL_FLAG       (2)
00050 #define GSS_C_REPLAY_FLAG       (4)
00051 #define GSS_C_SEQUENCE_FLAG     (8)
00052 #define GSS_C_CONF_FLAG         (16)
00053 #define GSS_C_INTEG_FLAG        (32)
00054 #define GSS_C_ANON_FLAG         (64)
00055 #define GSS_C_PROT_READY_FLAG   (128)
00056 #define GSS_C_TRANS_FLAG        (256)
00057 
00058 /*
00059  * Credential usage options
00060  */
00061 #define GSS_C_BOTH              (0)
00062 #define GSS_C_INITIATE          (1)
00063 #define GSS_C_ACCEPT            (2)
00064 
00065 /*
00066  * Status code types for gss_display_status
00067  */
00068 #define GSS_C_GSS_CODE          (1)
00069 #define GSS_C_MECH_CODE         (2)
00070 
00071 
00072 /*
00073  * Define the default Quality of Protection for per-message services.  Note
00074  * that an implementation that offers multiple levels of QOP may either reserve
00075  * a value (for example zero, as assumed here) to mean "default protection", or
00076  * alternatively may simply equate GSS_C_QOP_DEFAULT to a specific explicit
00077  * QOP value.  However a value of 0 should always be interpreted by a GSSAPI
00078  * implementation as a request for the default protection level.
00079  */
00080 #define GSS_C_QOP_DEFAULT       (0)
00081 
00082 /*
00083  * Expiration time of 2^32-1 seconds means infinite lifetime for a
00084  * credential or security context
00085  */
00086 #define GSS_C_INDEFINITE        ((OM_uint32) 0xfffffffful)
00087 
00088 
00089 /* Major status codes */
00090 
00091 #define GSS_S_COMPLETE          (0)
00092 
00093 /*
00094  * Some "helper" definitions to make the status code macros obvious.
00095  */
00096 #define GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_OFFSET      (24)
00097 #define GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET      (16)
00098 #define GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_OFFSET      (0)
00099 #define GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_MASK        ((OM_uint32) 0377ul)
00100 #define GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_MASK        ((OM_uint32) 0377ul)
00101 #define GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_MASK        ((OM_uint32) 0177777ul)
00102 
00103 /*
00104  * The macros that test status codes for error conditions.  Note that the
00105  * GSS_ERROR() macro has changed slightly from the V1 GSSAPI so that it now
00106  * evaluates its argument only once.
00107  */
00108 #define GSS_CALLING_ERROR(x) \
00109   ((x) & (GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_MASK << GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_OFFSET))
00110 #define GSS_ROUTINE_ERROR(x) \
00111   ((x) & (GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_MASK << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET))
00112 #define GSS_SUPPLEMENTARY_INFO(x) \
00113   ((x) & (GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_MASK << GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_OFFSET))
00114 #define GSS_ERROR(x) \
00115   ((x) & ((GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_MASK << GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_OFFSET) | \
00116           (GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_MASK << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)))
00117 
00118 /*
00119  * Now the actual status code definitions
00120  */
00121 
00122 /*
00123  * Calling errors:
00124  */
00125 #define GSS_S_CALL_INACCESSIBLE_READ \
00126         (((OM_uint32) 1ul) << GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_OFFSET)
00127 #define GSS_S_CALL_INACCESSIBLE_WRITE \
00128         (((OM_uint32) 2ul) << GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_OFFSET)
00129 #define GSS_S_CALL_BAD_STRUCTURE \
00130         (((OM_uint32) 3ul) << GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_OFFSET)
00131 
00132 /*
00133  * Routine errors:
00134  */
00135 #define GSS_S_BAD_MECH \
00136         (((OM_uint32) 1ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00137 #define GSS_S_BAD_NAME \
00138         (((OM_uint32) 2ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00139 #define GSS_S_BAD_NAMETYPE \
00140         (((OM_uint32) 3ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00141 #define GSS_S_BAD_BINDINGS \
00142         (((OM_uint32) 4ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00143 #define GSS_S_BAD_STATUS \
00144         (((OM_uint32) 5ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00145 #define GSS_S_BAD_SIG \
00146         (((OM_uint32) 6ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00147 #define GSS_S_NO_CRED \
00148         (((OM_uint32) 7ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00149 #define GSS_S_NO_CONTEXT \
00150         (((OM_uint32) 8ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00151 #define GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN \
00152         (((OM_uint32) 9ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00153 #define GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_CREDENTIAL \
00154         (((OM_uint32) 10ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00155 #define GSS_S_CREDENTIALS_EXPIRED \
00156         (((OM_uint32) 11ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00157 #define GSS_S_CONTEXT_EXPIRED \
00158         (((OM_uint32) 12ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00159 #define GSS_S_FAILURE \
00160         (((OM_uint32) 13ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00161 #define GSS_S_BAD_QOP \
00162         (((OM_uint32) 14ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00163 #define GSS_S_UNAUTHORIZED \
00164         (((OM_uint32) 15ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00165 #define GSS_S_UNAVAILABLE \
00166         (((OM_uint32) 16ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00167 #define GSS_S_DUPLICATE_ELEMENT \
00168         (((OM_uint32) 17ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00169 #define GSS_S_NAME_NOT_MN \
00170         (((OM_uint32) 18ul) << GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET)
00171 
00172 /*
00173  * Supplementary info bits:
00174  */
00175 #define GSS_S_CONTINUE_NEEDED   (1 << (GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_OFFSET + 0))
00176 #define GSS_S_DUPLICATE_TOKEN   (1 << (GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_OFFSET + 1))
00177 #define GSS_S_OLD_TOKEN         (1 << (GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_OFFSET + 2))
00178 #define GSS_S_UNSEQ_TOKEN       (1 << (GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_OFFSET + 3))
00179 #define GSS_S_GAP_TOKEN         (1 << (GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_OFFSET + 4))
00180 
00181 /* XXXX these are not part of the GSSAPI C bindings!  (but should be) */
00182 
00183 #define GSS_CALLING_ERROR_FIELD(x) \
00184         (((x) >> GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_OFFSET) & GSS_C_CALLING_ERROR_MASK)
00185 #define GSS_ROUTINE_ERROR_FIELD(x) \
00186         (((x) >> GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_OFFSET) & GSS_C_ROUTINE_ERROR_MASK)
00187 #define GSS_SUPPLEMENTARY_INFO_FIELD(x) \
00188         (((x) >> GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_OFFSET) & GSS_C_SUPPLEMENTARY_MASK)
00189 
00190 /* XXXX This is a necessary evil until the spec is fixed */
00191 #define GSS_S_CRED_UNAVAIL GSS_S_FAILURE
00192 
00193 #endif /* __PTLRPC_GSS_GSS_ERR_H_ */
